title: Grateful Dead Live at Santa Fe Downs on 1983-09-10
lineage: MAC > Nak CR7A w/ azimuth adjusted > Korg MR-1000 @ 5.8mhz > FLAC 24/96; Edited & Mastered in Audacity by Joe Noel, Flac 24/96; Checksum & tags created in xACT
description:
Set 1

The Music Never Stopped, They Love Each Other, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues-> Beat It On Down The Line, Tennessee Jed, Minglewood Blues-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Women Are Smarter-> Cumberland Blues, Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Drums-> The Other One-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> One More Saturday Night, E: Cold Rain & Snow

reviews.review_text: Another killer show This is the best sounding audience available.  Been waiting for these to surface for a long time.  Had these tapes, but they were really too worn out & a few generations too many for me to feel good about sharing here.  The mix is so good.  The right amount of crowd between songs etc. to get the real flavor of being there.  Music is fantastic.  Just sample the 'Rider' to see what I mean - if for some odd reason you have not experienced this show before.
